@Hand\_Bannana & NicodemusCromwell  
Loops only cause a draw if there's no way for them to end. A mandatory loop that will somehow break itself eventually will play out for however many steps that takes. In this case it breaks itself by causing your opponent to loose the game. If you have more than one opponent the loop will kill all of them, because [Sanguine Bond](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sanguine Bond) has you pick a target opponent each time it's triggered.  

The only way it would cause an infinite loop is if your opponent has some way of surviving unlimited life loss. Such as [Phyrexian Unlife](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Phyrexian Unlife).
